==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*awjō'', originally a substantive adjective of ''*ahwō'' ‘river’ ( > Old English [[ea|ēa]]), from Indo-European ''*əkʷā-''.  Cognate with Old High German [[ouwa]] (German [[Aue]] ‘meadow’), Middle Dutch [[ouwe]], Old Norse [[ey]] (Swedish [[ö]]).

